===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
In the {{w|oracle bone script}}, a {{liushu|p|nocap=y}} of a person holding something on their head with both hands. Possibly originally the same character as {{zh-l|*異}} (“person wearing a mask” or “person carrying something on their head”), see there for more.

Later, a {{liushu|psc|nocap=y}}, with {{och-l|異}} serving as the semantic (and also possibly phonetic) component, and either {{och-l|弋}}, {{och-l|𢦏}}, or {{och-l|之}} acting as a phonetic component.

